## Audit Checklist

### Story 4.1: List Pending Services
```typescript
// Playwright test:
await page.goto('/allocation');
await expect(page.locator('table')).toBeVisible();
const times = page.locator('td.departure-time');
await expect(times.first()).not.toHaveText('--:--');
```
- [ ] Service list/table visible
- [ ] Service Code column present
- [ ] Origin → Destination shown
- [ ] Distance (km) shown
- [ ] Departure time shown (NOT "--:--")
- [ ] Date filter works

### Story 4.2: Generate Train Recommendations
```typescript
// Playwright test:
await page.goto('/allocation');
await page.click('tr:first-child'); // Select service
await page.click('button:has-text("Recommend")');
await expect(page.locator('.recommendation')).toHaveCount({ min: 1 });
```
- [ ] Select service → Recommend button works
- [ ] Recommendations appear within 30 seconds
- [ ] Shows 5 ranked trains
- [ ] Each shows: Train ID, Score, Km delta, Dead running

### Story 4.3: Display Justifications
```typescript
// Playwright test:
await page.click('.recommendation:first-child');
await expect(page.locator('.justification')).toHaveCount({ min: 3 });
```
- [ ] Expand recommendation shows justifications
- [ ] At least 3 justification reasons
- [ ] Human-readable sentences
- [ ] Uses EN 15380 terminology

### Story 4.4: Confirm Allocation
```typescript
// Playwright test:
await page.click('.recommendation:first-child button:has-text("Assign")');
await expect(page.locator('.toast')).toContainText('assigned');
```
- [ ] "Assign" button visible
- [ ] Click creates allocation
- [ ] Success toast appears
- [ ] Service moves to Assigned list
- [ ] < 5 clicks to complete

### Story 4.5: Filter Trains by Criteria
```typescript
// Playwright test:
await page.click('[data-testid="filter-toggle"]');
await expect(page.locator('.filter-panel')).toBeVisible();
```
- [ ] Filter panel exists
- [ ] Fleet type filter works
- [ ] Depot filter works
- [ ] Km range filter works
- [ ] Status filter works

### Story 4.6: Solver Recommendation Engine
```bash
# API test:
curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/recommend \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"serviceId": "1", "candidates": ["train-1", "train-2"]}'
```
- [ ] Python solver returns recommendations
- [ ] Response includes top 5 trains
- [ ] Each has 3+ justifications
- [ ] Dead running km calculated
- [ ] Solver time in response

